Waking up throughout the night is normal. Most adults do it between two and six times per night—and if you’re a good sleeper, these wakings will be so brief that you likely won’t remember them, says Lynelle Schneeberg, a sleep psychologist and assistant professor of psychiatry at Yale Medicine.&nbsp;
But for some people, nighttime wakings are so intrusive that they experience what Schneeberg calls “the download.”
